# === PUBLIC-MIRROR SAFETY (read before editing) ===
#
# This working copy is Cayman's ENTIRE private ~/Projects workspace, but
# `origin` is the PUBLIC repo github.com/ChunkyTortoise/ai-redteam-notes.
#
# Strategy: ALLOWLIST. Ignore everything by default, then re-include ONLY the
# verified public red-team paths. Every new top-level entry is private by
# default and is NOT committable unless an explicit `!` line is added below.
# This failed safe once already (a near-miss that staged 5,786 private files
# incl. secrets). Do not switch to a denylist.

# 1) Ignore every top-level entry
/*

# 2) Re-include the verified public red-team surface (matches origin/main)
!/.gitignore
!/.github/
!/ATTACKS/
!/BOUNTIES/
!/CASE_STUDIES.md
!/CTF/
!/DETECTIONS/
!/EVALS/
!/LICENSE
!/Makefile
!/PUBLISHING.md
!/README.md
!/REPORTS/
!/REPRODUCE.md
!/RESEARCH-SUMMARY.md
!/SECURITY.md
!/WRITEUPS/
!/docs/
!/index.html
!/lab/
!/pipeline/
!/site/

# 3) Defense in depth: never commit secrets/junk even under an allowed path
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
**/.mcp.json
**/.mcp.json.bak
**/.jwt_secret
**/*.pem
**/id_rsa*
**/*.key
**/node_modules/
**/.DS_Store
